<P>In this voyage we took on board the passen|gers and crew of a ship consumed by fire, and set them on shore at Newfoundland, and soon after relieved another ship, where all on board were perishing for want of provisions. On board this last were three passengers, an old lady, her son, and a maid servant. They were barely alive when we met with them, and the old lady died that night. The youth and the maid went with us to my island, as did a young priest whom we took out of the other ship.</P>
