said she, he no makee good live? You tell me he is great, can makee kill when he will. Why he no makee kill when he serve him. He, no know? Yes, I answered, he knows and sees all things and hears us speak. What! returned she, he no hear you swear, curse, speak are great damn! Yes, yes, he hears it all, I cried. Where be then the muchee greate pow|er strong! He never makee kill, never angry when we do wicked, then he no good himself, or no great able. Yes my dear, says I, he does sometimes punish in this world, and many are cut off in their sins, and then go to hell, where they are miserable for ever. He no makee you dead! she returned, and you no tell him tank you for all that! I am an ungrateful dog that's true, I returned. I wish you make me know God, she replied, I no makee him angry; I no do bad wicked ting. I'll pray to God to teach you he replied; when she return|ed. He give all ting, then he make me good <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> I wish to be good; he spare me, no makee <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> me when I be good. Me take, think, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> him to be great God, me will tank <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> with you, my dear. Atkins said, that he could here for bear no longer but prayed with his wife. In a word, the poor woman, after some convers<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">ion with the priest, in which I wa<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> interpreter&punc; desired to be bant<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">ed <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> and she was afterwards <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> my Jack of all trades was <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> woman whom I had <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span">.</P>
